Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Most parameters are within normal limits. Notable findings include mild thrombocytosis, hyperglycemia (with normal HbA1c suggesting acute elevation), and dyslipidemia (elevated total cholesterol, LDL, triglycerides, and low HDL), which increase cardiovascular risk. Creatinine is slightly below the reference range but not clinically significant. Cardiac markers (NT-proBNP, troponin) are within expected ranges for age. Recommend clinical correlation for hyperglycemia and lipid abnormalities, and consider follow-up for cardiovascular risk management.
